item.description: "Life isn't about finding yourself. Life is about creating yourself." -- George Bernard Shaw

item.title: Kadena add a quote by Abraham Lincoln
item.description: "Folks are usually about as happy as they make their minds up to be." -- Abraham Lincoln

item.title: Kadena add a quote by Frank Herbert
item.description: "I must not fear. Fear is the mind-killer. Fear is the little-death that brings total obliteration. I will face my fear. I will permit it to pass over me and through me. And when it has gone past I will turn the inner eye to see its path. Where the fear has gone there will be nothing. Only I will remain." -- Frank Herbert

item.title: Kadena add a quote by Albert Einstein
item.description: "Great spirits have always encountered violent opposition from mediocre minds." -- Albert Einstein

item.title: Kadena add a quote by mahatma gandhi
item.description: "I will not let anyone walk through my mind with their dirty feet." -- mahatma gandhi

item.title: Kadena add a quote by Albert Einstein
item.description: "The intuitive mind is a sacred gift and the rational mind is a faithful servant. We have created a society that honors the servant and has forgotten the gift." -- Albert Einstein

item.title: Kadena add a quote by Joseph Addison
item.description: "Reading is to the mind what exercise is to the body." -- Joseph Addison

item.title: Kadena add a quote by Buddha Siddhartha Guatama Shakyamuni
item.description: "The secret of health for both mind and body is not to mourn for the past, nor to worry about the future, but to live the present moment wisely and earnestly." -- Buddha Siddhartha Guatama Shakyamuni

item.title: Kadena add a quote by Louise L. Hay
item.description:
"You have the power to heal your life, and you need to know that. We think so often that we are helpless, but we're not. We always have the power of our minds…Claim and consciously use your power.
" -- Louise L. Hay

item.title: Kadena add a quote by LOUISE L. HAY (FOREWORD) LOUIS PROTO
item.description: "Remember, you have been criticizing yourself for years and it hasn’t worked. Try approving of yourself and see what happens." -- LOUISE L. HAY (FOREWORD) LOUIS PROTO

item.title: Kadena add a quote by Wayne W. Dyer

item.title: Kadena add a quote by Orison Swett Marden

item.title: Kadena add a quote by Herbert N. Casson
item.description: "A true Leader asks advice, when he has time to think; but he never asks advice in a crisis. He acts" -- Herbert N. Casson

item.title: Kadena add a quote by Charles F. Haanel
item.description: "You can not entertain weak, harmful, negative thoughts ten hours a day and expect to bring about beautiful, strong and harmonious conditions by ten minutes of strong, positive, creative thought." -- Charles F. Haanel

item.title: Kadena add a quote by Albert Camus
item.description: "Don't walk behind me; I may not lead. Don't walk in front of me; I may not follow. Just walk beside me and be my friend." -- Albert Camus

item.title: Kadena add a quote by Mahatma Gandhi
item.description: "Live as if you were to die tomorrow. Learn as if you were to live forever." -- Mahatma Gandhi
